Important information

Safety Information

Please confirm the port of your laptop is MINI DP, MINI DISPLAYPORT or THUNDERBOLT 2.0

Product Description

Mini Displayport to HDMI VGA 2-in-1 Adapter

Mini DP adapter enables you to connect a Mini DP/Thunderbolt 2 compatible laptop to an HDMI or VGA equipped display, monitor, projector, TV.

The 2-in-1 adapter makes it fit for various kind of displays. Compatible with all Mini displayport laptops and HDMI/VGA equipped displays, monitors, projectors.

Thunderbolt 2.0 - Mini DP Compatible Devices

  • 2015 and before MacBook Pro, Mac Pro, iMac, Mac mini, MacBook Pro Retina; 2017 and before MacBook Air;
  • Microsoft Surface surface pro 1 2 3 4 5 6, Surface 3, Surface Book, Surface Laptop 2, Surface Studio; Does not support Surface Pro 7/Surface Book 2/Surface Studio 2, since they do not have Mini Displayport.
  • Lenovo Yoga, Lenovo ThinkPad X1 Carbon, X230/X240s, L430/L440/L530/L540, T430/T440/T440s/T440p/T530/540p, W530/W540, Helix;
  • Dell XPS 14/15/17(before 2016), Latitude E7240/E7440, Precision M3800;
  • Alienware 14/17/18; Acer Aspire R7/S7/V5/V7; Intel NUC; Asus Zenbook; HP Envy 14/17;
  • Google Chromebook Pixel; Cyberpower Zeusbook Edge X6; B87Toshiba Satellite Pro S500, Tecra M11/A11/S11; etc.

Not compatible:

  • Mac Book Air 2018/2019; Mac Book Pro 2016-2019; iMac 2016-2019; MAC mini 2005-2009,2018,2020
  • Surface Book 2/Surface pro 7,Pro x /Surface Laptop 3
  • Surface Go /Surface dock /Surface /Surface 2 /Surface Studio 2

Triple Shielding Transmits Stable Signal

The Thunderbolt adapter with triple shielding of ground wire and braid and aluminum foil, which could effectively prevent EMI and make sure a stable signal transmission between devices.

Free Drive, Plug and Play

No any driver or program required, saving time on installing a complicated driver before using; and no external power supply required.

Package Content

UGREEN gold-plated Mini Displayport to HDMI VGA video adapter x 1.

* If you are not sure if your device is compatible with this adapter, pls consult with us. *

*Important Note*

1.HDMI and VGA port can't be used simultaneously.

3.Compatible with Thunderbolt(1st Gen) and Thunderbolt 2, DO NOT compatible with Thunderbolt 3/USB-C port.

2.Only HDMI port could transmit audio and video, VGA interface could only transfer video.

3.Apple devices released before April 2010 do not support audio out and will not transmit sound from Mini DisplayPort.
